      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "@corsiKa It&#39;s not necessarily true that you don&#39;t want to &quot;Catch &#39;em all&quot;, it&#39;s just a different use case.  If you have a top-level loop or event handler (for instance, inside a thread&#39;s run) if you don&#39;t catch at least RuntimeException and log it, you will often miss the exception altogether AND silently break out of an important loop for what is often a one-time failure.  It&#39;s also really good for plugin functionality where you don&#39;t know what additional code might do or throw...  For top-down uses like these catching Exception is often not only a good idea but a best practice."
