    "question_id" : 1097527,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can also wrap the exception in another one AND keep the original stack trace by passing in the Exception as a Throwable as the cause parameter:</p>\n\n<pre><code>try\n{\n   ...\n}\ncatch (Exception e)\n{\n     throw new YourOwnException(e);\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 44652,
