    "score" : 6,
    "last_activity_date" : 1420659246,
    "creation_date" : 1420659246,
    "answer_id" : 27827221,
    "question_id" : 1097527,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>public int read(byte[] a) throws IOException {\n    try {\n        return in.read(a);\n    } catch (final Throwable t) {\n        /* can do something here, like  in=null;  */\n        throw t;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This is a concrete example where the method throws an <code>IOException</code>. The <code>final</code> means <code>t</code> can only hold an exception thrown from the try block. Additional reading material can be found <a href=\"http://www-01.ibm.com/support/docview.wss?uid=swg21386753\" rel=\"noreferrer\">here</a> and <a href=\"http://www.javac.info/Rethrown.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">here</a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2106355,
      "reputation" : 320,
      "user_id" : 1872605,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/turNN.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Sindre",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1872605/sindre"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 7,
    "last_activity_date" : 1730386754,
    "last_edit_date" : 1730386754,
    "creation_date" : 1514454538,
    "answer_id" : 48005172,
    "question_id" : 1097527,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Stack trace is preserved if you wrap the caught exception into another exception (to provide more info) or if you just rethrow the caught exception.</p>\n<pre><code>try{\n    ...\n}catch (FooException e){\n     throw new BarException(&quot;Some useful info&quot;, e);\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
